# Jira PM Brain (zara-jira-mcp)

124-tool MCP server for project management with AI intelligence and persistent memory.

## When to Use

Activate these tools when user asks about:
- Sprint status, Jira issues, team workload
- Risks, blockers, decisions, dependencies
- Retrospectives, planning, forecasting
- Team health, velocity, capacity
- Stakeholder reporting

## First Call

`jira_boards` — get board_id. Store it.

## Quick Reference

| Task | Tool |
|------|------|
| Standup prep | `pm_standup_prep(board_id)` |
| Sprint planning | `pm_planning_prep(board_id)` |
| Health check | `pm_sprint_health(board_id)` |
| Forecast | `pm_forecast(board_id, remaining_items:N)` |
| Record risk | `pm_record_risk(title, severity, owner, mitigation)` |
| Record decision | `pm_record_decision(title, decision, rationale)` |
| Record blocker | `pm_record_blocker(description, issue_key, owner)` |
| Exec report | `pm_exec_report(board_id)` |
| End sprint | `pm_snapshot_sprint(board_id, velocity:N)` |
| Anti-patterns | `pm_anti_patterns(board_id)` |

## Rules

1. NEVER `pm_dashboard` for executives — use `pm_exec_report`
2. Record decisions/risks/blockers immediately
3. `pm_snapshot_sprint` at end of every sprint
4. `pm_auto_detect_risks` weekly
5. Full docs: see SKILL.md
